						               													<description>Letter is an unusual word game.  As with many word games, there are letter tiles which are laid on a grid in order to form words.  What is unusual about Letter is that the letter tiles are different sizes: 1&amp;times;1, 1&amp;times;2, 1&amp;times;3, 2&amp;times;1, 2&amp;times;2, 2&amp;times;3, 3&amp;times;2, and 3&amp;times;3 (because orientation matters).  Words are identified by chaining along orthogonally adjacent sides of the letters.  As a result, the board can quickly come to look like quite a jumbled mess of letters with varied sizes, but this provides opportunities for lateral thinking in playing that next tile.  Each play initiates a Boggle-style word search, but with deference to the active player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Debuted in Essen 2008.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
